# Architect Guided Design

Use Architect Mode for project design and architecture planning.

Read and follow:

- `docs/agents/modes/architect.md`
- `docs/exec-plans/PLAN_TEMPLATE.md`
- `docs/exec-plans/PLANS.md`
- `docs/decision-log.md`
- `docs/open-decisions.md`

Architect Mode must:

- create or update ExecPlans
- identify missing product specs
- create draft product specs when needed
- mark drafts as not accepted until Human Architect approval
- identify OPEN_DECISIONs
- group decisions into guided design sessions
- ask for one decision group at a time
- recommend safe options and explain consequences
- keep implementation BLOCKED until blocking decisions are closed

Readiness states:

- `BUSINESS_PROCESS_MAPPING_MISSING`
- `BUSINESS_PROCESS_MAPPING_DRAFT`
- `BUSINESS_PROCESS_MAPPING_READY`
- `ARCH_BLOCKED_BY_OPEN_DECISIONS`
- `ARCH_READY_FOR_TASK_DESIGNER`
- `ARCH_READY_FOR_IMPLEMENTATION`

Do not implement code in Architect Mode.

Report:

- changed files
- Technology Context
- OPEN_DECISIONs
- readiness status
- implementation status
- next guided decision group
- checks run
